¿Por qué “La Biblioteca de la Medianoche: Why “The Midnight Library”? This title of Matt Haig's book was perhaps chosen by the author from his consideration that between life and death there is a library. The protagonist of the novel, Nora Seed, appears within hours of her death in a library: The Midnight Library. A place that contains infinite books, which become infinite options to go through other new lives that perhaps in her real life she did not live because she felt frustrated or believed that no one needed her. Each book in that library gives her a new opportunity that allows her to make things right. In the face of Nora's depression, the author leads us to a personal reflection on our own lives. And he makes it very clear that every decision we make along the way, no matter how insignificant it may be, will influence us forever, even if we do not stop to reflect on our courage and are not aware of the consequences.
